1 Overview Ciona RNA-seq time-series

We collected matching samples to measure the proteome and transcriptome at 8 time points. For the bulk mRNA-seq libraries, we followed a stranded protocol (first-strand). We used Salmon to map the reads to the reference transcriptome (KY21) and quantify gene expression. We used DESeq2 to normalize the expression data, and preprocessCore to quantile normalize. We collected two biological replicates: one subsampling the sample from proteomics and another from a different time series.

  • Install and load required libraries.
  • Prepare the count data and sample information.
  • Run the DESeq2 analysis.
  • Extract results for each contrast and create volcano plots.

# distribution_plot function
distribution_plot.fn <-
  function(dataset, stages_order_1, stages_order_2, title, subtitle, normalized = FALSE) {
    plot <- ggplot(dataset) +
      aes(x = factor(stage, level = stages_order_1), y = expression, fill = stage) +
      # aes(x = fct_inorder(stage), y = expression, fill = stage) +
      geom_violin(trim = FALSE, show.legend = FALSE) +
      scale_fill_manual(values = ciona_stages_rep_palette) +
      stat_summary(fun = "median", geom = "point", shape = 95, size = 10, color = "black", show.legend = FALSE) +
      labs(y = "log2 expression", x = "Developmental stage", title = paste(title, "by replicate"), subtitle = subtitle) +
      theme_pubr(x.text.angle = 45) +
      theme_personalised +
      theme(panel.grid.major.y = element_line(colour = "grey45", linetype = "dotted")) +
      dataset %>%
      separate(stage, into = c("stage", "rep"), sep = "_(?=[^_]+$)") %>%
      mutate(stage = factor(stage, level = stages_order_2)) %>%
      ggplot() +
      # aes(x= factor(stage, level = stages_order_2), y=expression, fill=stage) +
      aes(x = stage, y = expression, fill = stage) +
      scale_fill_manual(values = ciona_stages_palette) +
      geom_violin(trim = FALSE, show.legend = FALSE) +
      stat_summary(fun = "median", geom = "point", shape = 95, size = 10, color = "black", show.legend = FALSE) +
      labs(
        y = "log2 expression", x = "Developmental stage",
        title = paste(title, "by stage"),
        subtitle = subtitle
      ) +
      theme_pubr(x.text.angle = 45) +
      theme_personalised +
      theme(panel.grid.major.y = element_line(colour = "grey45", linetype = "dotted"))
      
    return(plot)
  }

# Average biological replicates
mean_by_repStage.fn <-
  function(dataset, column_order) {
    result <- dataset %>%
      pivot_longer(-gene_id, names_to = "stage") %>%
      separate(stage, into = c("stage", "rep"), sep = "_") %>%
      group_by(gene_id, stage) %>%
      summarise(mean = mean(value)) %>% # Calculate the row means for each stage by gene
      pivot_wider(names_from = stage, values_from = mean) %>% # Pivot the result to wide format
      dplyr::select(gene_id, all_of(column_order)) %>%
      ungroup()

    return(result)
  }

# cumulative frequency
plot_cumfreq.fn <- 
  function(data, x_1, x_2, color, title) {
    ggplot(data) +
      stat_ecdf(aes(x = {{x_1}}, y = 1 - ..y..), geom = "step", size = 1, color = color,pad = FALSE) +
      stat_ecdf(aes(x = {{x_2}}, y = 1 - ..y..), geom = "step", size = 1, color = color,, pad = FALSE) +
      scale_x_log10(
        breaks = scales::trans_breaks("log10", function(x) 10^x),
        labels = scales::trans_format("log10", scales::math_format(10^.x))
      ) +
      labs(y = "Cumulative frequency", x = "Gene expression (TPM)", title = title) +
      coord_equal(ratio = 6) +
      theme_personalised
  }

# scatterplot
plot_scatterplot.fn <- function(data, x, y, color, title) {
  ggplot(data, aes_string(x = x, y = y)) +
    # geom_point(size = 0.6, color = color, alpha = .5) +
    # geom_hex(alpha = .5,fill = color) +
    geom_point(shape = '.', col = color) +
    stat_cor(aes(label = ..r.label..), size = 5,label.x.npc = 0, label.y.npc = 0.7
             # label.y = 4.6
    ) + 
    # stat_cor(aes(label = ..r.label..), size = 5,label.x.npc = "center") + #, label.x = 1e-1, label.y = 1e3) +
    annotate(geom = "text", x = 5.5, y = 90000, size = 7, label = title) +
    scale_x_log10(
      limits = c(1,1e5),
      breaks = scales::trans_breaks("log10", function(x) 10^x),
      labels = scales::trans_format("log10", scales::math_format(10^.x))
    ) +
    scale_y_log10(
      limits = c(1,1e5),
      breaks = scales::trans_breaks("log10", function(x) 10^x),
      labels = scales::trans_format("log10", scales::math_format(10^.x))
    ) +
    annotation_logticks(sides = "lb") +
    labs(x = "Repl 1", y = "Repl 2", 
         # title = title
    ) +
    coord_equal() +
    theme_personalised 
}

# heatmap
heatmap_function <- function(matrix,title, legend) {
  # Calculate min & max
  min_value <- min(matrix)
  max_value<- max(matrix)
  middle_value <- (min_value + max_value) / 2
  
  # color scale
  color_scale <- colorRamp2(c(min_value, middle_value, max_value), c(
    "#A7D3D4FF", "#F1F1F1FF", "#E4C1D9FF"
    #"#DC876CFF",  "#FEFEFEFF", "#ADD0B5FF"
    ))

heatmap <- Heatmap(
    matrix,
    name = "Correlation",
    col = color_scale,
    show_row_names = TRUE,
    show_column_names = TRUE,
    cluster_rows = FALSE,
    cluster_columns = FALSE,
    column_dend_height = 50,
    column_title = title,
    row_title = "",
    row_names_side = c("left"),
    column_title_gp = gpar(fontsize = 16),
    row_title_gp = gpar(fontsize = 16),
    column_names_rot = 45,
    row_names_rot = 0,
    cell_fun = function(j, i, x, y, width, height, fill) {
      grid.text(x = x, y = y, label = round(matrix[i, j], 2), gp = gpar(fontsize = 10))
    }, 
    heatmap_legend_param = list(title = paste(legend," correlation"), direction = "horizontal"))
  
  return(heatmap)
  # draw(heatmap,heatmap_legend_side = "bottom", annotation_legend_side = "bottom")
}

1.5 PCA

###############################
#### TPM PCA
###############################

# TPMFilt_ciona.df  => >5 TPM rowSum 
TPM_pca <- TPMFilt_ciona.df |> column_to_rownames(var = "gene_id") |> mutate(across(where(is.numeric), ~ log2(. + 1)))

# eg the TPM.df hass the columns order unf_1 unf_2 fer ... and not unf_1 fert_1 
column_to_stage_mapping <- c("unfE_1" = "unfE","unfE_2" = "unfE","fertE_1" = "fertE","fertE_2" = "fertE","cell16_1" = "cell16","cell16_2" = "cell16","iniG_1" = "iniG","iniG_2" = "iniG","latN_1" = "latN","latN_2" = "latN","midTII_1" = "midTII","midTII_2" = "midTII","latTII_1" = "latTII","latTII_2" = "latTII","larva_1" = "larva","larva_2" = "larva")

pca.res <- prcomp(t(TPM_pca),center = T,scale.=F, retx=T) # here scale.=T or F does change the interpretation; it's center by default
pc.var<-pca.res$sdev^2 # sdev^2 captures these eigenvalues from the PCA result
pc.per<-round(pc.var/sum(pc.var)*100, 1)
pca.res.df <- as_tibble(pca.res$x) |> 
  mutate(group= column_to_stage_mapping[colnames(TPM_pca)]) |> 
  dplyr::select(group, everything())

pca.res.df$group <- factor(pca.res.df$group, levels = c("unfE", "fertE", "cell16", "iniG", "latN", "midTII", "latTII", "larva"))

pca.plot <- ggplot(pca.res.df) +
  aes(x=PC1, y=PC2, label=column_to_stage_mapping, color = group) +
  geom_point(size=4) +
  scale_color_manual(values = ciona_stages_palette) +
  xlab(paste0("PC1 (",pc.per[1],"%",")")) +
  ylab(paste0("PC2 (",pc.per[2],"%",")")) +
  # ggrepel::geom_label_repel()+
  # labs(title="PCA Ciona") +
  coord_fixed() +
  labs(color = "Stage - TPM") +
  theme_personalised +
  theme(legend.position = c(0.5,0.5))

pca.plot
cairo_pdf("plot_rna_PCA_TPM.pdf", width=8.5, height=5.6)
print(pca.plot)
invisible(dev.off())

ordStage <- c("unfE_1","unfE_2","fertE_1","fertE_2","cell16_1","cell16_2","iniG_1","iniG_2","latN_1","latN_2","midTII_1","midTII_2","latTII_1","latTII_2","larva_1","larva_2")

### Compute pairwise correlation values and then order matrix
TPM_cor_pearson <- cor(log2.filtTPM.df[,-1],method = "pearson")
TPM_cor_spearman <- cor(log2.filtTPM.df[,-1],method = "spearman")

TPM_cor_pearson <- TPM_cor_pearson[ordStage,(ordStage)]
TPM_cor_spearman <- TPM_cor_spearman[ordStage,(ordStage)]
#__________________________________________________________________________

rld_cor_pearson <- cor(rld_mat,method = "pearson")
rld_cor_spearman <- cor(rld_mat,method = "spearman")

rld_cor_pearson <- rld_cor_pearson[ordStage,(ordStage)]
rld_cor_spearman <- rld_cor_spearman[ordStage,(ordStage)]
#__________________________________________________________________________


### plot heatmap
heatmap_TPM_pearson <- heatmap_function(TPM_cor_pearson,"TPM","Pearson")
heatmap_TPM_spearman <- heatmap_function(TPM_cor_spearman,"TPM","Spearman")
#__________________________________________________________________________

heatmap_rld_pearson <- heatmap_function(rld_cor_pearson,"DeSeq","Pearson")
heatmap_rld_spearman <- heatmap_function(rld_cor_spearman,"DeSeq","Spearman")

# pearson comparison TPM vs DeSeq
ht_list_pearson = heatmap_TPM_pearson + heatmap_rld_pearson

plot_pearson =draw(ht_list_pearson, 
     column_title = "Pearson",
     column_title_gp = gpar(fontsize = 16),
     heatmap_legend_side = "bottom", 
     annotation_legend_side = "bottom") 
# spearman comparison TPM vs DeSeq

     column_title = "Spearman",
